list: Shrimp Scampi: A classic pairing with pasta and garlic bread.
Shrimp Alfredo: Creamy and delicious with fettuccine.
Pasta with a White Sauce: The buttery flavor of shrimp complements alfredo or cheese-based sauces.
Lemon Pasta: A light and refreshing option.
Pasta with Shrimp and Pistachio Pesto: Adds a unique flavor and texture.
Rice Pilaf: Try couscous, quinoa, or orzo for a flavorful base.
Cheesy Tex-Mex Rice: A hearty and flavorful option.
Portuguese-Style Mint Rice: Adds a unique taste.
Fried Rice: With green onions, garlic, and other vegetables.
Roasted Vegetables: Lemon-pepper asparagus or a medley of seasonal vegetables.
Steamed Broccoli or Asparagus: A healthy and simple side.
Caprese Salad: Fresh mozzarella, basil, and tomatoes.
Salads and Slaws: Cucumber Caprese salad, broccoli and cauliflower coleslaw, or a tangy carrot slaw.
Creamy Coconut Rice: Goes well with coconut shrimp.
Crispy Sweet Potato Fries: A great accompaniment to coconut shrimp.
Grits: Shrimp and grits is a classic Southern dish.
Corn on the cob and boiled potatoes: Steamed shrimp with cocktail sauce and saltine crackers pairs well with these.
French Fries, coleslaw, and hushpuppies: Go well with fried shrimp.
Garlic Bread: A simple and satisfying addition.
